<body>

    

    <div class="recipe-container">
        <h1>Fluffy & Crispy Poori Recipe</h1>
       
       

        <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
        <ul class="ingredients-list">
            <li>2 cups Whole Wheat Flour</li>
            <li>1/2 tsp Salt</li>
            <li>3/4 cup Water (as needed)</li>
            <li>1 tsp Oil or Ghee</li>
            <li>Oil for Deep Frying</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Instructions:</h2>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>In a bowl, mix wheat flour, salt, and 1 tsp oil.</li>
            <li>Add water gradually and knead into a smooth, firm dough.</li>
            <li>Cover and let the dough rest for 20 minutes.</li>
            <li>Divide into small balls and roll into small circles.</li>
            <li>Heat oil in a deep pan, then fry each poori until golden and puffed.</li>
            <li>Drain on a paper towel and serve hot with potato masala or chana curry.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

</body>
